To qualify as a provider-sponsored integrated health delivery network, an applicant shall submit information acceptable to the department to satisfactorily demonstrate that the provider-sponsored integrated health delivery network:
Is licensed and in good standing with the licensure boards for participating providers;
Has demonstrated the capacity to administer the health plans it is offering;
Has the ability, experience, and structure to arrange for the appropriate level and type of health care services;
Has the ability, policies, and procedures to conduct utilization management activities;
Has the ability to achieve, monitor, and evaluate the quality and cost effectiveness of care provided by its provider network;
Is financially solvent;
Has the ability to assure enrollees adequate access to providers, including geographic availability and adequate numbers and types;
Has the ability and procedures to monitor access to its provider network;
Has a satisfactory grievance procedure and the ability to respond to enrollees' inquiries and complaints;
Does not limit the participation of any health care provider in its provider network in another provider network;
Has the ability and policies that allow patients to receive care in the most appropriate, least restrictive setting;
Does not discriminate in enrolling members;
Participates in coordination of benefits;
Uses standardized electronic claims and billing processes and formats; and
Discloses to the cooperative reimbursement arrangements with providers.

Provider-sponsored integrated health delivery networks shall be subject to the provisions of this subtitle, and to the following provisions of this chapter, to the extent applicable and not in conflict with the expressed provisions of this subtitle:
Subtitle 1 -- Scope of Code;
Subtitle 2 -- Commissioner of the Department of Insurance;
Subtitle 3 -- Authorization of Insurers and General Requirements;
Subtitle 4 -- Fees and Taxes;
Subtitle 5 -- Kinds of Insurance--Limits of Risk--Reinsurance;
Subtitle 6 -- Assets and Liabilities;
Subtitle 7 -- Investments;
Subtitle 8 -- Administration of Deposits;
Subtitle 9 -- Agents, Consultants, Solicitors, and Adjusters;
Subtitle 12 -- Trade Practices and Frauds;
Subtitle 14 -- KRS 304.14-120 to 304.14-130 and 304.14-500 to 304.14-560;
Subtitle 25 -- Continuity of Management;
Subtitle 33 -- Insurers Rehabilitation and Liquidation;
Subtitle 37 -- Insurance Holding Company Systems; and
Subtitle 99 -- Penalties.
